  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7, and take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Soak your <strong>skewers</strong> in <strong>cold water</strong> (this stops them from burning whilst cooking!)</p><p>Cut your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into fries, then add them to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong>, <strong>dried oregano</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>– these are your <strong>herby fries</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-2-1720443311702-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-2-1720443311702-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-2-1720443311702-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-2-1720443311702-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-copy-2-1720443311702-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until crisp – these are your <strong>herby fries</strong></p><p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>free range chicken breast portion[s]</strong> into bite sized pieces</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-2-1720443320191-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-2-1720443320191-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-2-1720443320191-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-2-1720443320191-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-copy-2-1720443320191-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and grate (don't chop!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>chopped chicken </strong>and<strong> half </strong>the <strong>grated garlic </strong>to a large bowl with your <strong>cumin seeds</strong>, <strong>ground</strong> <strong>smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>half</strong> your <strong>red wine vinegar </strong>(save the rest for later!)<strong> </strong>and a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and season with a very generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>– this is your <strong>marinated chicken</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-copy-2-1720443324743-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-copy-2-1720443324743-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-copy-2-1720443324743-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-copy-2-1720443324743-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-copy-2-1720443324743-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Thread the <strong>marinated chicken</strong> onto the <strong>soaked</strong> <strong>skewers</strong> – these are your <strong>marinated chicken skewers</strong></p><p>Transfer the <strong>marinated chicken skewers</strong> to a<strong> tin foil</strong>-lined baking tray</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 22-25 min or until the chicken is slightly charred and cooked through (no pink meat!) – these are your <strong>chicken souvlaki skewers</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
